<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1878,1903]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin prefix 
<emphasis box="[915,985,1879,1902]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">magni</emphasis>
- and the adjective 
<emphasis box="[1200,1295,1878,1902]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">hamatus</emphasis>
, referring to the large hook of the aedeagus.
